		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>28 West 9<hi rend="underline">th</hi> St. New York City</placeName>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>April 10<hi rend="underline">th</hi> 1866</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Dr. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> &#38; Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Mr. Sternberger</persName><lb/> having very kindly informed me that<lb/> he had mentioned my name to you&#44;<lb/> I embrace the opportunity of addressing<lb/> you for the second time&#44; and in<lb/> so doing forwarding a letter of<lb/> introduction from <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Sollas</persName> of<lb/> <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>.  This I had hoped to<lb/> present in person&#44; but will not<lb/> be enabled to visit <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> for a few days.  You will<lb/> doubtless recollect the first<lb/> time I had the honor of writing<lb/> you&#44;</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>you&#44; was in reference to the<lb/> &#34;Guide&#34; a Literary Periodical<lb/> of which I was the Editor.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">And now Rev Sir&#44; I beg<lb/> leave to inform you that I<lb/> am in search of an appoint&#44;<lb/>ment either as Lecturer&#44; Teacher&#44;<lb/> or Hazan.  I feel sure if<lb/> you will kindly give me your<lb/> valuable aid &#38; advice&#44; I<lb/> shall soon meet with my<lb/> desires.  I am well known<lb/> here to the <persName>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> D<hi rend="sup">rs</hi>. Raphael</persName>&#44;<lb/> <persName>Isaacs</persName> &#38; <persName>Lyons</persName>.  I have already<lb/> instituted <sic>enquiries</sic> respecting<lb/> the following appointments<lb/> Teacher in <placeName>Memphis Tn</placeName><lb/> &#34; &#34; <placeName>Shreveport La</placeName><lb/> &#34; &#34; <placeName>Norfolk Virg</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>Lecturer in <placeName>Boston Mass.</placeName><lb/> I am told by <persName>Mr. Sternberger</persName><lb/> that there are others of<lb/> which you are acquainted<lb/> May I therefore solicit the<lb/> favor of your informing me<lb/> as to their directions with<lb/> the necessary particulars.<lb/>  In the hope of soon seeing<lb/> you and thanking you<lb/> in person<lb/> I am<lb/> Respectfully<lb/> Your obt Ser.</p>
				<p><persName role="author">R Dl. Leevier</persName></p>
				<p>Please address<lb/> <persName role="author">Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. R. Dl. Leevier</persName><lb/> <placeName>28 West 9th St.<lb/> near 6th Avenue<lb/> New Yk.</placeName></p>
		</body>
